list.house_rules: While we welcome families and groups, we are not a party house and we ask that guests be respectful of the peaceful nature of our neighborhood.
list.description:
Bright and airy Los Angeles ranch estate, perfect for family getaways and retreats.  Our home is minutes from Hollywood and Downtown LA, but hidden away from all the hustle and bustle with easy access to the mountains and hiking trails.  Gorgeous chef's kitchen, pool, patios, outdoor dining, and mountain views.

We have a large, private, ranch-style estate, situated in the foothills of the Angeles National Forest.  It's a quiet, secluded hideaway in horse country that's deceptively close to some of the best parts of Los Angeles.  

The house is a 4000-square-foot estate on an acre of land.  Downstairs you'll find a formal living room, plus two TV/family rooms, one bedroom, and a gigantic chef's kitchen.  We have several coffee makers, and standard kitchen appliances.  Guests are welcome to use the kitchen in its entirety. Upstairs are the remaining 5 bedrooms, including a spacious master with sunken bathtub and rainfall shower.  The king and queen mattresses are Tempurpedic, and the twin mattresses are gel-based memory foam, so everyone will get a good night's sleep. 

Outside, you'll find the patio, pool, and backyard.  The backyard is tree-covered and perfect for yoga, sports, and naps.  The entire property is gated and private.  There is a charcoal bbq - you'll just need to bring your own charcoal!

Our interaction with guests is typically minimal - but we are available when needed.  We have family that live next door and are happy to help and will answer any questions that may come up.

We live in a small community at the base of the Angeles National Forest, surrounded by horse-friendly estates.  You'll definitely see horses around, and there are lots of options for horse-back riding nearby.  However, we're still close to places like Hollywood and DTLA, with easy access to places like Universal, Santa Clarita / Magic Mountain, Burbank, etc, so you get the best of both worlds here.  There are plenty of grocery stores and restaurants nearby, but you're still offered the privacy and quiet of a hillside estate.  We're very close to hiking trails, Kagel Canyon, Wildwood, Big Tujunga Canyon, Switzer, etc.

Depending on traffic, we are located about:

15 minutes from Universal Studios
20 minutes from Hollywood
25 minutes from Magic Mountain
35 minutes from DTLA
45 minutes from Santa Monica
45 minutes from the beaches

There is rarely traffic in our area, but as you get closer to Hollywood, Santa Monica and Central LA, you'll have more during peak times.
list.summary: Bright and airy Los Angeles ranch estate, perfect for family getaways and retreats.  Our home is minutes from Hollywood and Downtown LA, but hidden away from all the hustle and bustle with easy access to the mountains and hiking trails.  Gorgeous chef's kitchen, pool, patios, outdoor dining, and mountain views.

It is therefore important that your reservation reflect the number of people in your party AND the number of beds those people will require so that the house can be properly prepared for your arrival. You will be able to access your entire area and private garden space.

Interaction would only be if we see you as you're entering through the gated driveway, other than that we give you privacy. Always available for help if you need anything by text. Most of the time we are away at work so the property is pretty quiet during the day.

Cozy bright safe small (500sq ft) private studio close to many Attractions, Resturants, and Recreation activities. It has private entrance and Kitchenette.

This space is a small 500 square feet apartments, but it has everything you need. The kitchen is completely stocked with utensils, pots, and pans. There are even some spices as well.

When you arrive, our gate is easy to open and walkway is best for luggage unloading. There is a convenient fridge, stove, and cabinet where you can store any goodies.

We live right around the corner and are  available assist you during your stay. We are California natives therefore we may be knowledgeable about events and special attractions you may not have heard of. If needed, we can make suggestion to make the most out of your trip!

We are located in the Sylmar. A quiet old Ranch community. 
We are located in the Sylmar. A quiet old Ranch community 
 We are  15 minutes from Universal Studios,  Magic Mountain, Hurricane Harbor, Discovey Cube, San Fernando Mission, Nettercutt Museum and many other Attractions and activities. There are beautiful parks with many Recreational activities available like swimming, hiking trails, Parasailing, horseback riding, and even disc golf. There is a also golf course within a mile. There are many restaurants within walking distance and unique eateries too like Sushi Latin Fusion and authentic taco stands.

We are located one mile from the Sylmar Metrolink station which can take you to Burbank Airport in less than 20 minutes. It also runs all the way to downtown Los Angeles Union Station and an easy visit to Downtown Los Angeles. There is a bus station right on the corner of our property that can take you to downtown Los Angeles and two other places in San Fernando Valley such as the Northridge Mall. It is located walking distance to several supermarkets, fast food places, and restaurants. You are also about a mile away from beautiful parks and nearby hikes. We are centrally located to many of the major freeways and the UCLA Olive View Medical Center.

list.name: Light Filled Modern Two Bedroom in NOPA
list.description:
This is a newly constructed, impeccably clean, two bedroom that is only a few blocks away from some of SF's finest shops, restaurants, and bars.  High ceilings, tall windows, and skylights means the space is soaked in sun. It has high-end finishes, including hardwood floors and marble countertops.  Professionally furnished, with a mix of vintage and custom furniture and art. It also features a large television, Apple TV, and a Sonos sound system throughout the home.

The downstairs bedroom has a new queen-size Casper mattress, with high-end linens, on a Room & Board storage bed. The upstairs loft bedroom is outfitted as a home office with a new sleeper sofa with 4" memory foam mattress. The kitchen is fully outfitted with plates, glasses, cooking utensils, and everything else needed to cook up a feast. Appliances are all high end, including an Italian Bertazzoni range. The bathroom has custom walnut cabinets, marble tile flooring, and amazing water pressure. The living room has a custom sofa, genuine mid-century refinished lounge chairs, a large flat screen TV with surround sound Sonos speakers, and a cushy custom leather ottoman to put your feet up. Numerous plants fill every corner in every room.

You will have sole use of the entire apartment. It does not have a garage, but you can easily connect with public transportation (MUNI), use ride share apps (Lyft or Uber), bike, or walk to anything you’ll need.  The apartment is on the major tech bus lines and a 20 minute Uber ride to downtown.

The unit is located in San Francisco's NOPA neighborhood. It is walking distance to numerous famous restaurants, bars and coffeeshops. It is 2 blocks from Alamo Square, and 2 blocks from the Panhandle. It is also a 10 minute walk to the Haight/Ashbury Neighborhood.

The unit is close to several bus lines. A Lyft or Uber downtown is an 18 minute ride away. Parking is street only and a temporary permit is required to park for more than 2 hours at a time. We recommend not having a car if possible as there are no close public parking lots.

For longer term stays we may have to come in once a week to water the plants. We can do this while you are away.

Our neighbor’s kids bedroom is right outside the patio, so it is my preference that you are not in the patio area after 10pm. list.description:
*Please send me an inquiry telling me a little bit about yourself and purpose of trip before booking.  I would like to know a little bit about my guests before accepting any bookings.  Thank you!*

The perfect San Francisco getaway retreat is waiting for you at this high-end, newly remodeled, beautifully furnished, 2000 square foot penthouse! 

Whether you want a nature-based, escape vacation with parks and wilderness close by, a family friendly experience, or you prefer an exciting on-the-town adventure with dinners out and nightlife, this location has it all! Visitors may walk, run or bike ride through Golden Gate Park. Families have playgrounds and sightseeing attractions nearby.  Located in Haight Ashbury and near the Castro and NOPA neighborhoods, the restaurants, bars, coffee shops, stylish and unique boutiques will keep you entertained and discovering all that is San Francisco. Walk the neighborhood and view some of the most gorgeous Victorian houses that San Francisco has to offer.

This penthouse apartment, gorgeously remodeled with high end finishes and furnishings, is filled with natural light, 11 foot ceilings, and 2000 square feet of space plus a 700 square foot outdoor deck! You get all modern conveniences while retaining typical San Francisco Victorian charm and detail. The flat has two large bedrooms with king size beds, an office with a queen size high end pull out couch, two full bathrooms, a  full living room with 50” high def TV, a full dining room, a reading nook and views of quintessential San Francisco Victorians. 

You’ll enjoy cooking in the chef’s kitchen with high end stainless steel appliances including 5 burner stove, dishwasher, large refrigerator and freezer, double sink, microwave, coffee maker, and cookware items. The master bedroom has an en suite bathroom with radiant heated floors, a modern bathtub and separate shower, plus double sinks.  The master bedroom is extremely quiet with plush carpet to block out any city sounds. Both bedrooms have king size beds and the office has a queen size leather pull out couch and a desk from which to work. The formal dining room has a large table that seats 8 persons. The living room and master bedroom both have a large flat screen 50” high def TV with cable and access to hundreds of streaming movies.  There is wi-fi throughout the house and an iPad for your use filled with tourist and sightseeing information as well as a Chrome OS PC for internet browsing. There is a washer and dryer in the unit and laundry soap. The deck has afternoon sunshine, electric BBQ, outdoor dining table and sectional sofa for lounging.


The apartment sleeps 6 persons; will consider a 7th if it is an infant. The apartment has digital keypads/door locks with codes that expire after checkout so rest assured that keys to the apartment aren't in the hands of others. 

Parking on the property is available for an additional daily fee of $15/day/car (one garage space and one driveway space) and large SUVs and trucks will not fit (maximum car width of 75 inches with the mirrors in).  There are 2 bicycles to rent daily with a credit card.  Any parties you plan on hosting with more than 8 people must be pre-approved by owners in writing.  The apartment has 35 stairs to get to the flat.  Once inside there are no stairs.


Though located in the world-famous, historic Haight-Ashbury district, the Castro, Hayes Valley, Inner Sunset, Alamo Square, Cole Valley and Duboce Triangle are all easy to reach by car, foot, or public transportation.  Perfect for business travelers, couples, families, short-term corporate housing, and vacationers. Dogs/Cats allowed with prior permission.  It’s a dog paradise with numerous dog parks within walking distance.

Guests will enjoy professional cleaning, high-thread count linens and plush towels.

3. Pets need to be approved before making a reservation. If approved a security pet deposit will be requested. 

4. NO SMOKING PROPERTY

If PG&E (Pacific Gas and Electric) monthly bill goes over $90 you will be responsible to pay the difference. This amount will be calculated and prorated according your stay and will be deducted from the security deposit. 
If you do an smart and conscious usage of utilities you won't need to pay any difference.

6. CLEANLINESS. All debris, rubbish and discards must be placed in a trash receptacles, and soiled dishes should be placed in the dishwasher when leaving the apartment. Please run the dishwasher prior your departure. 
Extra cleaning charges will apply if proeprty is not left in good cleaning standards. The cleaning fee you have paid is to tied up the property, wash towels and bedding and general cleaning, not to clean dishes nor to perform a deep cleaning. Basically the look of the proeprty needs to be the same as the one when you moved in.
list.description:
This property is only available with a minimum stay of one month.

This historic Victorian sits on a hillside overlooking the City and Marin Headlands to the north from a large private deck.

This historic Victorian sits on a hillside overlooking the City and Marin Headlands to the north from a large private deck. It also has views of a neighbor flower garden from the kitchen and dining area. It has a fireplace with a gas insert and hardwood floors. The kitchen is large and includes a dishwasher, stove/oven and microwave. Bedroom has full size bed and private bath. Bathroom has old style combination tub shower. Note on the pictures that the bedroom has no door.

You will have access to the entire property.

I'm here in San Francisco, just let me know if you need anything.

HAIGHT ASHBURY This vacation rental is located in Haight Ashbury, exactly in between Upper Haight and Lower Haight. Any day of the week, the Upper Haight is filled with a potent mix of locals and tourists. Many shops are geared towards luring visitors with some kind of reflection of the neighborhood's storied past. The carnival-like energy and strong vintage atmosphere comes through everywhere, from the clothing shops to the ornate Victorian architecture.

Less touristy and more low-key than the Upper Haight, this is an eclectic alternative to the Mission, very similar in style. The diverse restaurants, shops and salons cater to residents more than visitors. Walking distance to tennis courts located in a beautiful park. The park is also great for jogging and evening walks. Yoga and massage studios are nearby. Moreover, walking distance to shopping in the lively Haight-Ashbury and Castro neighborhoods. Washer/Dryer located in the building.

ARKING SITUATION

There is free street parking around the unit. It is not metered and no permit is needed.

PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION & DISTANCES

Union Square is 2.3 miles away from the property: By car or taxi: 12 min. By public transportation: 20 min. Take Bus #6 direction downtown and stop at Powell St. Walking distance: 40 min.

The Moscone Center is 2.4 miles away from the property: By car or taxi: 12 min. By public transportation: 20 min. Take Bus #6 direction downtown and stop at Powell St. Walking distance: 42 min.

Fisherman's Warf is 3.7 miles away from the property: By car or taxi: 16 min. By public transportation: 45 min. Take the Muni line N direction Caltrain and stop at Embarcadero. Then take Muni line F direction Fisherman’s Wharf and stop there.

The SFO Airport is 14.2 miles away from the property: By car or taxi: 25 min. You can also book a shuttle service. By public transportation: 50 min. Take BART at the airport direction East Bay, and stop at Civic City Center. Then transfer to Muni and take line N outbound and stop at Duboce.

content.space:
Master Bedroom: King Bed | Bedroom 2: Queen Bed | Bedroom 3: Queen Bed, Twin Trundle Bed | Bedroom 4 (1st floor): Queen Sleeper Sofa 

Nestled in the pristine Newport community, this spacious home is designed to impress with modern elegance and comfortable furnishings. 

Just steps from your home-away-from-home is the shared outdoor pool and spa. Dive into relaxation in this pristine body of water or enjoy a soothing soak in the jacuzzi for optimal holiday relaxation. 

When you're not lounging poolside, unwind in the living area, featuring plush sofas, a stereo, smart home system, and a Smart TV with cable channels and a large projector screen. 

You'll want to put your culinary skills to the test in the high-end kitchen, adorned with stainless steel appliances, sleek countertops, a breakfast bar, and a farmhouse sink. Enjoy your home-cooked cuisine at the 2-person breakfast bar or at the dining room table with seating for 6. 

For a front-row seat to colorful Arizona sunsets, retreat upstairs to the private rooftop patio, with seating for 2 and picturesque Tempe views. The property also features a second-floor balcony - the perfect place to jumpstart your day with a cup of coffee or end it with an evening nightcap.

Retire to the well-appointed master bedroom, offering a king-sized bed and an en-suite bathroom with a large shower and bathtub. Sleep will come easy in Bedrooms 2 and 3, boasting high-quality memory foam queen mattresses. Additional sleeping can be found in the downstairs 4th bedroom with high-end foam mattress queen-sized sleeper sofa.
content.access: Guest has access to the whole house. Just make it your own home in the dessert.

content.neighborhood_overview: Visit boutiques, museums, galleries, live theatre, gourmet fare and more in these lively cities, or head out into nature for more adventure. Downtown Tempe is just a stone's throw away, and Old Scottsdale is only 15 minutes away.

Rental car is highly recommended. Although uber/Lyft are also very convenient to use in town. There’s also free flash to go to ASU and downtown. 
We have two bikes you can use for free.

content.name: Haight Ashbury
content.description:
Years ago, the Haight-Ashbury of San Francisco scene had a long-gone '60s and ‘70s hippie culture.  However, over time the Haight has changed.  But save for a few hippie memorabilia, today the Haight has a whole new vibe.  Although there are some fragments of flower-power, incense-burning, acid-dropping, peace-and-love-vibing era that can be purchased at smoke shops along the neighborhood, today the neighborhood is different. With exclusive boutiques, high-end vintage-clothing shops, second-hand stores, Internet cafés and hip restaurants having all settled in, this reinvented area stands out as one of San Francisco's commercial centers.  

What makes the Haight unique is its just-rolled-out-of-bed vibe during the day, which provides a perfect opportunity for lazing around in cafés and bookstores.  Weekends can get quite crowded with shoppers and brunch seekers during the day and club-goers at night. Neo-punks, club kids, fashionistas, tourists and neighborhood locals also fit in here, whether they have come to get a new piercing, grab a burrito or just enjoy some fun people-watching from a café.  But there are two distinct areas of the Haight: The Upper Haight, which stretches from Stanyan to Masonic, which is known as the shopping zone, though it deteriorates a bit where it stretches toward Golden Gate Park. While, the Lower Haight, roughly Divisidero to Webster is a more diverse neighborhood with a stony feel. While it has been an alternate nightlife hub for years, the Lower Haight has become a main attraction for DJs and ravers with an attraction to dance-music and clubs.

neighborhood.description:
Hayes Valley is a neighborhood in the Western Addition district of San Francisco, located between popular districts of Alamo Square and the Civic Center. In this area is a wide variety of architectural homes such as Victorian, Queen Anne, and Edwardian townhouses which are mixed with classy boutiques, restaurants and public housing complexes.  Twenty years ago, the thought of finding one of San Francisco's ultra-chic streets in Hayes Valley would have been unheard of. The area located on the areas surrounding Van Ness performing-arts district and the Western Addition around Laguna Street, was not always so popular. This area was a constant reminder for opera and symphony patrons of the city's homeless and drug problems. But over the past decades, Hayes Valley has beautifully transitioned into a simple hub for haute couture.  

Today, Hayes Valley is a modern haven for window shoppers and restaurant-goers, who walk the streets to enjoy trendy fashion boutiques, SoHo-style funky art galleries, high-end interior-decorating shops, top-notch restaurants and buzzing nightspots.  The success of Hayes Valley's current commercial district was revitalized in part by the destruction caused by the 1989 earthquake to the Central Freeway, which was an eyesore and created noise pollution that kept businesses and people away. Not long after that part of the freeway came down, the community began to transform, and commerce slowly moved in.  Surprisingly, Hayes Valley has managed to retain a sense of community and a nonexclusive feel despite the quick buildup and high price tags, where tourists also target this area, specifically for the shopping.
neighborhood.name: Hayes Valley

list.title: Rental - Single Family Detached, Other - Austin, TX
list.description: A soft contemporary newer build presenting smart executive living designs complimenting its extraordinary downtown location. Life in the center of downtown E Austin provides unparalleled urban vibes; walking to Lady Bird Lake, morning coffee, afternoon lunch venues or evening soul soothing dining, arts and clubs. Like a good handshake, Willow's grip on a downtown lifestyle is firm, authentic and beyond impressionable. *Pets considered on case by case basis.Masterfully executing open concepts, main floor living basks in volume and natural light. The clever layout of the entertainer's kitchen provides circular prep and presentation on multiple sides. Integrated outdoor living shoulders the open dining area serving up a stunning blend of outdoor lounging and dining with custom expansive deck designs.Second story living provides an unparalleled master bedroom redefining retreat. A massive space defined by volume,celestial window architecture, a fully appointed master en-suite, and a walk-in master closet. Secondary bedrooms play a duet with the master in volume and light. The upper level second living area provides an extra multi-purpose space affording choices for the work at home executive. With a full appliance package and tech smart features, Willow delivers on all levels of downtown executive living adventures. Like a good handshake, you know it's right.

api_list.name: Investment Likelihood
api_list.description: Get investment likelihood score for a property, read more about the score in API details section.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://mashvisor-api.p.rapidapi.com/ml/investment-likelihood"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "mashvisor-api.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())
